{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:job.22",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 22,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 22",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 22 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.22.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:1",
      "text": "Then Job answered and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.22.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:2",
      "text": "Is it not the Lord that teaches understanding and knowledge?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.22.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:3",
      "text": "For what matters it to the Lord, if thou wert blameless in thy works? or is it profitable that thou shouldest perfect thy way?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.22.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:4",
      "text": "Wilt thou maintain and plead thine own cause? and will he enter into judgment with thee?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.22.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:5",
      "text": "Is not thy wickedness abundant, and thy sins innumerable?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.22.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:6",
      "text": "And thou hast taken security of thy brethren for nothing, and hast taken away the clothing of the naked.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.22.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:7",
      "text": "Neither hast thou given water to the thirsty to drink, but hast taken away the morsel of the hungry.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.22.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:8",
      "text": "And thou hast accepted the persons of some; and thou hast established those that were already settled on the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.22.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:9",
      "text": "But thou hast sent widows away empty, and hast afflicted orphans.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.22.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:10",
      "text": "Therefore snares have compassed thee, and disastrous war has troubled thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.22.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:11",
      "text": "The light has proved darkness to thee, and water has covered thee on thy lying down.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.22.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:12",
      "text": "Does not he that dwells in the high places observe? and has he not brought down the proud?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.22.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:13",
      "text": "And thou hast said, What does the Mighty One know? does he judge in the dark?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.22.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:14",
      "text": "A cloud is his hiding-place, and he shall not be seen; and he passes through the circle of heaven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.22.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:15",
      "text": "Wilt thou not mark the old way, which righteous men have trodden?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.22.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:16",
      "text": "who were seized before their time: their foundations are as an overflowing stream.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.22.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:17",
      "text": "Who say, What will the Lord do to us? or what will the Almighty bring upon us?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.22.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:18",
      "text": "Yet he filled their houses with good things: but the counsel of the wicked is far from him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.22.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:19",
      "text": "The righteous have seen it, and laughed, and the blameless one has derided them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.22.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:20",
      "text": "Verily their substance has been utterly destroyed, and the fire shall devour what is left of their property.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.22.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:21",
      "text": "Be firm, I pray thee, if thou canst endure; then thy fruit shall prosper.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.22.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:22",
      "text": "And receive a declaration from his mouth, and lay up his words in thine heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.22.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:23",
      "text": "And if thou shalt turn and humble thyself before the Lord, thou hast thus removed unrighteousness far from thy habitation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.22.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:24",
      "text": "Thou shalt lay up for thyself treasure in a heap on the rock; and Sophir shall be as the rock of the torrent.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.22.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:25",
      "text": "So the Almighty shall be thy helper from enemies, and he shall bring thee forth pure as silver that has been tried by fire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.22.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:26",
      "text": "Then shalt thou have boldness before the Lord, looking up cheerfully to heaven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.22.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:27",
      "text": "And he shall hear thee when thou prayest to him, and he shall grant thee power to pay thy vows.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.22.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:28",
      "text": "And he shall establish to thee again a habitation of righteousness and there shall be light upon thy paths.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.22.29",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:29",
      "text": "Because thou hast humbled thyself; and thou shalt say, Man has behaved proudly, but he shall save him that is of lowly eyes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.22.30",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:30",
      "text": "He shall deliver the innocent, and do thou save thyself by thy pure hands.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
